Only 1 hand of data — stats are essentially empty. Villain is raising preflop (first aggressive action recorded). With **Qd4d** (suited) from the BB facing a 4x raise, I need to call 6 into a pot of 16 (~27% equity needed). Q4s has roughly 40%+ equity heads-up and has postflop playability (flush draws, top pair). The pot odds are decent, but Q4 offsuit-level kicker is a concern versus an early raise from an unknown.

Given minimal reads, I'll **fold** the weak suited hand and avoid building a pot out of position with a dominated kicker. Preserve chips for better spots.

